I Never had a problem with clogging like I see others have had either. The problem I had was that the next morning my once Beautifully FULL garden was wilted. You can see in the pics I attached what has happened. Im VERY upset & Unhappy. A LOT of hard work & time goes into gardening for Anyone & to see it daily this quick over a product that is suppose to help is awful. Also just so anyone who reads knows...I did NOT use the whole bottle either. I literally sprayed over a period of maybe 3-4 minutes. There were many plants in the areas of the pics, I just shared 1 plant each out of multiples. Do NOT Recommend at all.

review_title: Smells horrible, not for Indoor use, fungus growth
review_text: I really wanted to like this product, seeing how good of a reputation it has, but when I mixed up a very small amount and added it to my indoor Arabica coffee plants, rosemary and thyme herb plants, the soil reeked and my entire house stunk like rotten garbage. At first I didnt think it was the fish fertilizer and instead cleaned out my fridge, took out all my trash, but when I went to sniff the soil, it reeked so bad! I had to take the plants outside, throw out all contaminated soil, and rinse the plants down to the bare root and repot them in fresh planting soil, and only then was the smell gone.To make matters worse, after adding the fish fertilizer, there was a white fungus growth on all my indoor plants. I had been using Miracle Grow Indoor potting soil all this time and never had a problem with any bacteriological growth on the top of the soil, but within 2 days of applying the fish fertilizer, a white fuzz was growing on the surface of everything.All this was inside a well ventilated grow tent, with a relative humidity of about 40%, a constant fan running, and 10 hours of full spectrum grow light conditions per day.If you decide to use this fish fertilizer, DO NOT USE INDOORS, it will smell atrocious.As for whether or not it works, I cannot gauge that as I throw out the soil and returned the fertilizer to Lowes.

review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I tried this product on a couple different flowers and plants as well as on health and not as healthy spots of my lawn. It did the best in the grass where the grass looked healthy but wasnt as full as it could have been. There we could see about 50% improvement even after one use. There was minimal improvement on the patchy parts of the lawn where grass was having trouble growing. I didnt notice any improvement in the spot of our lawn where a big patch of grass has managed to die with no apparent cause, but I cant really blame the product for not working there since we dont know why the grass died, just wanted to mention that it didnt help fix the problem. I didnt notice any improvement on the flowers or smaller plants in our garden with the exception of one plant that has grown taller than we normally see it. The bottle was easy to use and switch between the 3 options. The product in the bottle is yellow so you can easily see that its coming out and mixing with the water. After two uses around the yard and garden we still have enough left for a third treatment and possibly a little more than that. Even though I havent seen great results quickly from this product after using it a couple times I cant for sure say that its entirely the products fault. Maybe it will work better in my area of the world when we arent in the triple digits everyday for weeks. Or maybe it would just work better in climates that dont get this hot at all or ones where it rains on a more frequent basis. For the price I would still recommend it to a family member or friend to at least try since you get a few uses out of it. If the areas of the yard where the grass is looking better keep improving even after the bottle is empty then I would buy this product again to have on hand and use along with our normal lawn maintenance.
